author: Rick Coleman
title: Don Bosco blows by Dunkerton 76-0
text:
Don Bosco blows by Dunkerton 76-0 - KWWL - Eastern Iowa Breaking News, Weather, Closings Member Center: Don Bosco blows by Dunkerton 76-0 Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> More >> 
In 8 man the third ranked Don Bosco dons rolling toward a district 5 crown meets a Dunkerton team tonight with just one win. Don Bosco head coach Colby Yoder looking very relaxed before the start of this game and for good reason the Dons have it under control.. 
Early in the first quarter--Joel Sweeney slashes off tackle eight yards to the endzone-- 8-0 Don Bosco... 
The Dons cheerleaders getting some early airtime... 
Just a couple of minutes later Don Bosco quarterback Nick Mangrich hits Dylan Reiher with a 15 yard touchdown pass--16-0 dons. 
The next score comes on a botched snap by Dunkerton punter Jackson Hoeft-- he gets sacked in the endzone for a safety-- 18-0 Don Bosco. 
Later Joel Sweeney gets his second touchdown of the first quarter on this 20 yard dash...26-0 Don Bosco. 
Dunkerton produces a highlight--quarterback Alex Stumme goes up top--- and Kaleb Cox makes a pretty one handed catch--- and nearly scores --but Sweeney makes a touchdown saving tackle-- the Raiders drive would stall... 
Nick Mangrich scores on this big run to make it 34-0 Don Bosco with three minutes left in the first quarter--the powerful Dons roll 76-0.
